the virtio output is not from the geneve tunnel. it looks like pnat has changed the output interface from the virtio to the ethernet. i would have tought it would be preferable for the pcap trace to have the ethernet interface, since that is the interface on which the packet ultimately left the system.
this case might be better fixed by running interface output features before the pcap trace.

I was thinking the code in this node/function vnet_per_buffer_interface_output_node may not need to add the pcap trace. This code is enabled by the tunnel interfaces via this call       vnet_set_interface_output_node. I think we want to retain the call to pcap trace in this node vnet_interface_output_node. The latter node is for all device drivers, virtio-x-output, vhost-x-out, and avf-x-output, etc. But still, I am worried about the consequences of removing the pcap trace in vnet_per_buffer_interface_output_node. So my safer fix is to not add the pcap entry when it is already added. It is not the best fix, but it is safe from regressions. I am open to alternative fix which does not introduce regressions.
